rComments: For whoever left the comment below, Im pretty sure we were in the same class and sorry bud but I got an A+. Valencia respects effort. Show up to class, come to office hours and she will take the time to get to know you. Class definitely isnt a bird, if you hate math, there is some basic math. Nothing difficult, just keep up and youll be fine.
teacherRatingTags: ['Clear grading criteria', 'Beware of pop quizzes', 'Accessible outside class']

rComments: I'm pretty sure I was one of the best students in the class and I got a B-. I am 150% sure that first year astronomy is not supposed to have a 3hr exam that half the class doesn't even finish on time. Or a midterm that has an average of a D+ for the same reason. That being said, she's highly knowledgeable and a good lecturer. Inspiring in ways.

DV is one of the strongest lecturers at UTSC. She makes a strong effort to listen to students; it's easy to talk to her. Her informative lectures move at a great pace. She didn't follow a particular textbook; you need to attend lectures and take careful notes to succeed. The assignments/evaluations are consistent with lecture notes. Great Teacher!
